cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is focused on adversarial attacks on machine learning models, particularly statistical classifiers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses attacks on privacy of training data, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of images in benchmark comparisons suggests the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely. The paper also discusses the use of hyperparameters and computational complexity, which suggests the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is possible. Finally, the paper discusses the distinction between robust classification and anomaly detection, which suggests the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also possible.
